 more than any others.<br>
<br>
I guess there'll always be *some* group of people that'll annoy me in any online game I play.  On Vallon it was the xteaming crew, and now on Sullon it's the "training is a legal tactic!!" crew.  <br>
<br>
Granted everyone is really smooshed right now and there's not much room for people to hunt, but I've never seen so much training (and stupid /ooc) in my life.  A group comes along and wants a spawn, so they train stuff on the current group without even ASKING them anything.  A group of idiots trains SGs onto the dock area in Oasis because that's <i>their</i> area.  What?!?!?!<br>
<br>
Who are these morons?  They're the same people that were shady on Vallon, Rallos, Karana, and Bertoxxulous, but now they think Verant has given them a license to exploit on Sullon.  The "training is legal" thing is one of the worst things Verant did to pvp (in a team environment).  On Rallos you can kill those morons and it's over.  On a team server though you just have to live with it.<br>
<br>
Granted, most of the extreme idiots will realize over time that no one wants to group with them and their reputation will kill them as a guild.<br>
<br>
The ultimate:  A lvl five "good" player training FOUR sand giants in NRo killing just about every player in the zone at some point or another.  He was level five, so no one could attack him, and what did he care if he died?  He's only level 5. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udypp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dypp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/01 11:58:47 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My own team is my own worst enemy</span><hr size=1> or the lvl 1 newt in the S Qeynos bank doorway blocking mostly newt players in trying to get plat to let them out.. saying anything was allowed as long as he didn't swear<br>
<br>
as you say no one could kill him.. which is Verant's answer to the lack of rules<br>
<br>
Itsy - Neutral - Anarchia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/01 2:53:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My own team is my own worst enemy</span><hr size=1> This is why i feel monks are the most powerful class on the server, they have a way of dealing with everyone -- even people who they're not allowed to kill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaximilean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maximilean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/01 3:15:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fansy</span><hr size=1> I was in Nro too, trying to level; the level 5 good bard named Fansy really ticked me off; he killed half the folks in Nro it seems.  He ran right by me with his SG train, but I managed to duck into the tunnel.  He was there for AGES, no sign of being bored.  <br>
<br>
I feedbacked and petitioned it, customer support or no - there is no way to deal with a level 5 griefer through PVP, so it's Verant's job IMO.  I hope noone is going to contend that invincible Selo'd bards training 4 sand giants around through all the derv camps for kicks and giggles is just part of the game.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukordesh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kordesh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/01 3:39:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..........</span><hr size=1> &quot;The ultimate: A lvl five &quot;good&quot; player training FOUR sand giants in NRo killing just about every player in the zone at some point or another. He was level five, so no one could attack him, and what did he care if he died? He's only level 5. &quot;<br>
<br>
Yep thats Fansy. I have Fansy and Pansie up on www.badgamers.com currently. After having my entrie group and myself killed twice in a span of 5min during is last train I whent on a crusaid of reporting, petitioning, and e-mailing to get this @#%$ banned. This has been goig on for 4 days. Now I don't know about you. But 4 days of training SGs on people and not being able to be trained back AND being purposely under the PvP enabler so there is no recorse seems like it should be bannable under harrassment. I mean 4 days! Yesterday I was talking with a guide and he said the GMs knew about it. Ya they know about it but are they going to do anything!? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/01 5:35:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..........</span><hr size=1> Yup, that's the guy.  The stupidest thing is that sometimes you can hear the giants coming and sometimes you can't.  It seems to me that you can hear them when they're just walking around, but when they start running in pursuit of someone they quiet down hehe.  <br>
<br>
/shrug  <br>
<br>
This guy just better never level up over 5 or he's in trouble.  He's building a rep he won't be able to drop. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukelthana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelthana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/01 5:49:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..........</span><hr size=1> Think it's reasonable to send Verant a petition suggesting that blue-server 'Play Nice' rules be applied to the level 1-5 folks, since they are essentially non-PvPs? An important part of PvP servers is that actions have consequences and the lowbie immunity to punishment, be it from players or GMs, kind of contradicts that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/01 10:55:20 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..........</span><hr size=1> They need to eliminate the sanctuary level protection to players who leave their newbie yard.  It is getting exploited and badly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugrinkle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grinkle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/9/01 7:24:06 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..........</span><hr size=1> /agree Lisboa.<br>
<br>
Or just eliminate it entirely.<br>
<br>
On a team server, I felt there was enough 'cover' for me to get to L6 quickly even w/o sanctuary.  I got PK'd about a half dozen times before hitting L6, but thats far and away the lesser of two evils.<br>
<br>
One char per account and no PK level restriction make the santuary much less needed / relavant on Sullon anyway, IMO.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udarkennvelgarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkenn Velgarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://home.earthlink.net/~rosebug67/_uimages/Innoruuk03.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/9/01 10:57:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://darkenn.homestead.com/files/inny.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..........</span><hr size=1> <br>
&quot;This guy just better never level up over 5 or he's in trouble. He's building a rep he won't be able to drop.&quot;<br>
<br>
Who's to say he'll ever level past 5?  He can just keep his bard at 5 and keep doin the crap that he's doin.  <br>
<br>
I'm not a pvp'er here.  I just read the boards a lot.  With the new rules on Sullon, crap like this will happen.. its a damn shame.  Maybe Verant will wake up.. but probably not, they just seem to make pvp worse.<br>
<br>
..  just my thoughts here.. u can ignore the bluebie if ya want.  :P<br>
<br>
-Darkenn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uflapjax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flapjax</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/9/01 11:27:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE</span><hr size=1> Yep.  Verant made a strong attempt to win the race but fell short of the finish line with Sullon Zek.  Its a shame.  Now they are talking about a 'roleplay' server but without PvP.  Grrrrrr, when will they get it right?<br>
<br>
<img src=http://members.home.net/humblebee/eq/flamer.jpg> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/9/01 3:41:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE</span><hr size=1> Kelthana, that is an excellent suggestion with a valid argument to support it.<br>
<br>
I will /feedback that when I log on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/01 7:58:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE</span><hr size=1> There is a new post at EQ.com.<br>
<br>
They will be enabling all levels to pvp as soon as they enter a mid level adventure zone. This means no more invincable travel. You go to WC, you can die by anyone, level 1 or not.<br>
<br>
Oasis, N ro, all of these count as mid level zones. EC would be low level, as would Nektulous I guess. Going to make things pretty interesting again heh.<br>
<br>
-Anni <p>Stalker Of Sullen Zek.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uitzena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Itzena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/01 7:57:45 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://strike9.com/eq/Itzena/fullsize/anthy16t.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE</span><hr size=1> I wonder how many times someone like Fansy will have to be rooted in front of their train before they figure out that their circumstances have undergone a rather significant change? <br>
<br>
Actually snare or darkness might be better, just to watch them ever-so-slowly trying to escape their train...and failing.<br>
<br>
Vindictive? Moi?<br>
